Member of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.familjen.dk">  Familjen </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Bristlebane Server<br>
<br>
&quot;Who ever heard of a hafling overlord, anyway?&quot;<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=keaneabrams>Keane Abrams</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/3/03 2:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5415.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Half Ling Zek Armor</span><hr size=1> You will be able to wear enchanted dwarven plate as a cheaper alternative to Fierce Heraldic. You will also be able to wear the non diety cultural Brellium Plate which has similiar AC but less stamina and hps than the Fierce gear.<br>
<br>
Being a halfling rallos zek warrior gives you many options.<br>
<br>
 <p><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=174524"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.shatteredsword.com/sigs/keane.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lling>Lling</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/03 11:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5415.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Half Ling Zek Armor</span><hr size=1> In all honesty, most of our alliance MTs still wear a lot of pieces of FH. Some have even passed on ornate molds because their legs are &quot;good enough&quot;. Anything dwarven crafted might be a &quot;cheaper option&quot; but I'd just save up and get the real thing if you are serious about your armor. You'll just have to upgrade from dwarven to FH anyway and FH doesn't waste any points on mana - it all goes to HP.<br>
<br>
The best pieces, in my opinion, are the bracers (the saves plus the HP are very nice), the legs, and the shoulders, then work up from there. The prices should not be too bad with blue diamonds dropping so frequently in the elemental planes. The toughest component to get would be the essence of sunlight.  You would make any human smith VERY happy if you added some of that as part of the purchase price.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=271264"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.members.cox.net/angelarenee2/EverQuest/llingsig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sisthar>Sisthar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.bellsnwhistles.com/abul/1abu049.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/03 1:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5415.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Trouble is</span><hr size=1> My trouble so far is I really want to see the stats etc on the FH and prices I can expect to pay on Veeshan, I have not found any of them at everlore.com or eqprices nor have I seen any in the bazaar. I just want to see what I should be saving for, I have good armor to last me well into the 50's right now from friends that decked me out and my warrior is only 18. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lling>Lling</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/03 5:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5415.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Trouble is</span><hr size=1> Stats:<br>
<br>
visor AC 12, AGI 5, HP 60 <br>
gorget AC 14, AGI 5, HP 50 <br>
cloak AC 16, DEX 5, AGI 5, HP 80 <br>
belt AC 19, AGI 5, HP 80 <br>
