<br>
As a halfling, you cannot smith anything worthwhile (halflings get cultural tailoring as opposed to cultural smithing), so you *will* have to make a human smith.<br>
<br>
Estimates show about 6 months of farming to PL smithing the inexpensive way or about a 400k initial outlay of pp to do it quickly. Smithing is one of the hardest tradeskills to raise since they changed the trivials almost a year ago. It took me about 90k to get to 250 back when it was cheaper and easier.<br>
<br>
With blue diamonds more plentiful (and therefore prices dropping all the time), it is nowhere close to cheaper to take up smithing and make it yourself. You'd be better off finding a GM human smith on your server, approaching them politely, and working out some sort of a deal. Some smiths will do the combines for a fee if you bring them all the materials.<br>
<br>
Now if you *really* want to be a blacksmith, I would never discourage that. I think it is fun but not everyone finds it so or has that kind of patience. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=271264"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.members.cox.net/angelarenee2/EverQuest/llingsig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tarskxev>TarskXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/03 7:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5415.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> A full set of FH can be costly, but quite honestly, you don't need all the pieces, and some are more inferior than others.<br>
<br>
I don't know what your stats are like right now, but for example, you'd get more HP from a pair of Chok Spaulders than from the FH shoulders. I wouldn't wear the FH BP over my Thurg BP - Thurg gives me more HP. IMO, too many of the FH pieces have AGI and DEX and not enough STA on them. The cloak is nice raw HP for a backslot, but it's a 3-ring piece so people tend to charge for it. A Hiero cloak (If that's not where your haste is) is probably a good alternative, etc etc.<br>
<br>
Mix and match it, and with the new dyes, you don't even have to look like a reject from a charity store! <p>--<br>
